# Release & News Announcements

How `{{PROJECT_NAME}}` announces releases and notable news on external channels. This is a
**human-published** step by design: like opening a PR or publishing a GitHub Release, the
agent prepares the draft and a human presses send. Nothing here bypasses the
[`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md) §6.1 / §11 agent-vs-human boundary.

## Channels

| Channel | Handle / target | Mode |
|---|---|---|
{{#EACH_ANNOUNCE_CHANNEL}}| {{name}} | `{{handle}}` | `{{mode}}` |
{{/EACH_ANNOUNCE_CHANNEL}}

`mode` is `draft` (agent writes a draft the maintainer posts) or `manual` (maintainer writes
it entirely). No channel is `auto` unless an explicit, reviewed automation exists with the
credentials scoped to it.

## When to announce

- **Every release** that closes a milestone or ships a user-visible change (a `MINOR`/`MAJOR`,
  or a notable `PATCH` such as a security fix).
- **Notable news** between releases only when it matters to users (a major roadmap commitment,
  a deprecation notice). Routine internal work is not announced.

## What an announcement contains

1. One-line headline: what changed and why a user cares.
2. The version and a link to the GitHub Release / `CHANGELOG.md` entry.
3. 2–4 highlights (features, fixes, breaking changes) in plain language.
4. A call to action (upgrade, read the docs, give feedback) and the canonical repo link.

**Language.** The on-disk draft is **English** (the §2 rule). A human may localize the wording
per channel/audience when posting; that localization is not committed to the repo.

## Procedure (per release)

1. After the release PR is merged and the GitHub Release is published, the agent drafts the
   announcement text per channel under the release notes (or a scratch file the maintainer
   copies from) — **drafts only**.
2. The maintainer reviews, localizes if desired, and posts to each `draft`/`manual` channel.
3. Record nothing secret in the repo (no tokens/webhook URLs in committed files — keep those
   in GitHub Actions secrets or the maintainer's password manager).

## Boundary

| Action | Who |
|---|---|
| Draft the announcement text (English, per channel) | Agent |
| Localize, schedule, and **post** to each channel | **Human** |
| Hold the channel credentials / webhooks | **Human** (or scoped CI secret) |
